detail.content: WEEKEND INTENSIVE IN ORTHOPEDIC PHYSICAL THERAPY, Module 10: Movement Gait - FRIDAY AND SATURDAY                  WEEKEND INTENSIVE IN ORTHOPEDIC PHYSICAL THERAPY, Module 10: Movement Gait - FRIDAY AND SATURDAY     EARN YOUR CEUs at NYU in an immersive Friday through Saturday two-day format.      The Department of Physical Therapy’s innovative series of weekend intensives  provides advanced training in orthopedic practice to physical therapists in an immersive Friday/Saturday format.      *Friday, June 12, 2015 – 6:00 pm – 8:30 pm    *Saturday, June 13, 2015 – 8:00 am – 5:00 pm    ﻿Module 10: Movement Gait Wen Ling, PT, Ph.D.   Smita Rao, PT, Ph.D.   Todd Wilkowski, PT, OCS, SCS      - State the theoretical basis, principles and techniques of kinesiological      electromyography      - Critically analyze a research article related to kinesiological electromyography      - The concept of practice variability and its implications for  physical therapy      - Identify potential clinical scenario appropriate to be examined by kinesiological          electromyography      - Review  three-dimensional kinematics and kinetics of gait      - Use hardware and software at the Arthur J. Nelson Human Performance lab for      motion analysis and to measure plantar load  distribution. Develop a critical      understand of issues in data  acquisition and analysis      - Review  clinical applications of gait  analysis  for recent literature      Register online or for more information, email Peggy Dadaille or call 212-998-9429. NYU is an approved sponsor of the mandatory continuing education hours for licensed physical therapists required by the New York State Education Department.    Graduate credit is also available through the 12-month Clinical Residency Advanced Certificate Program in Orthopedic Physical Therapy, which prepares students for the APTA Clinical Specialist Exam.
